This paper deals with the medium access control (MAC) for vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) communications, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of path loss and fading, which are typical topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new access method for V2V communications, which can be considered as a system-level design problem (cs.SY). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are typical topics in mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and physics and society (cs.PF).
